<li id="cite_note-50"><b><a href="#cite_ref-50" title="">^</a></b> This was the turning radius of a 109, meaning that both aircraft, if necessary, could turn together at high speed(Bungay 2000, p. 259).</li>
<li id="cite_note-86"><b><a href="#cite_ref-86" title="">^</a></b> This same sort of warning was provided to North Vietnam by Soviet "spy trawlers" during the <a href="/wiki/Vietnam_War" title="Vietnam War">Vietnam War</a>.</li>
